author: @shumetietefera527
text: Using fit_transform() on both the training and test data separately is not recommended. The purpose of the fit_transform() method is to compute the necessary parameters (e.g., mean and standard deviation for standardization) based on the training data and then apply the transformation. Using it separately on the test data might lead to information leakage, where the transformation is influenced by statistics computed from the test set, potentially compromising the generalization performance of your model. @1:03, U used fit_transform() for test data too!!! It's OK as you already told as the main concept in the first example
